Tiger Game Day Info:
We are so excited to welcome fans to another year of Tiger Football!! There will be some changes to our entry policy. We ask you that you please follow each policy that is put in place. They are as Follows:
•All spectators will enter through the main gate on the Tennis Courts.
•The Nettleton Fans will enter through one line(Left Side) •Hatley fans will enter on the other side. (Right Side)
•Our gate will open at 5:45 to allow time for seating and social distancing.
•YOU MUST HAVE A MASK ON TO ENTER!
Please follow strict social distancing guidelines. Thank You for your support of the Nettleton Tigers!! #NettyPride

#ELEVATE
Justin K. Hollis
Principal

post_text:
We wanted to update everyone on yearbooks. We have been getting a lot of questions about when the books will be in. Unfortunately, because of Covid-19 and the printing company being in Texas, production was put on hold during the shelter in place order. Please bare with us as this is out of our control. We will keep you posted on when we will be able to distribute them following the CDC and NSD guidelines, once they are in.

At this time, they are supposed to have opened back up and we are scheduled to receive our books sometime in June. We were not given a specific date.

We can’t wait for you to see all that this book has to offer, as it is definitely a piece of history.

As for extras, we won’t know exactly how many will be available for purchase until the books are delivered. However, they will be first come first serve and the cost is $90.

If you have any questions please email Mrs. Jolly at tjolly@nettleton.k12.ms.us

From the office of the Superintendent:

Governor Reeves has announced that all schools will remain closed the rest of this school year. School district officials will work on a plan to continue providing learning opportunities, see what graduation options we might have for seniors, and discuss if our feeding program can restart while keeping everyone safe. We will provide more information at a later time. Thank you for supporting our school district!

From the office of the Superintendent:

School district officials will work on a plan to continue providing learning opportunities, see what graduation options we might have for seniors, and discuss if our feeding program can restart while keeping everyone safe. We will provide more information at a later time. Thank you for supporting our school district!

post_text:
From the superintendent's office:

The goal of the Shelter In Place order made by the governor is to limit contact with individuals from April 3 to April 20 so that MS may slow the spread of the COVID-19 virus. The point is for individuals to stay at home with only a few exceptions. Beginning Monday, April 6, the Nettleton School District has, after very serious consideration, decided to suspend its Feeding Program at least through the duration of the Shelter In Place order. This will help protect our staff and hopefully help keep them safe during this time. All school buildings will be closed. Staff will be available through email. Teachers will continue to work from home and be available through the avenues they have already set. There are plenty of online learning opportunities on our website. Please adhere to the directions we have been given statewide so that we can go back to our normal way of life as soon as possible.

Tim Dickerson
Superintendent, Nettleton School District
(662) 963-2151
www.nettletonschools.com

post_text:
Nettleton School District
Foodservice Information
COVID-19 School Closure

During the period of school closure, Nettleton School District Foodservice Department
will provide meals for students.
The meals will be curbside pickup and will be located at the awning between Nettleton
High School and Nettleton Upper Elementary School.
• Week of March 30 - April 3,
o Monday - Friday, lunches will be available from 11 am - 1 pm

SCHEDULE CHANGE

• Beginning Monday, APRIL 6, the schedule will change as follows:
o Pickup days will be Monday, Wednesday, and Thursday: 11 am - 1 pm
▪ Monday, 2 breakfasts and 2 lunches per child (Mon. & Tues. meals)
▪ Wednesday, 1 breakfast and 1 lunch per child
▪ Thursday, 2 breakfasts and 2 lunches per child (Thurs. & Fri. meals)
▪ There will be NO Tuesday or Friday pickups
A child must be present in the vehicle to pick up a meal.
This program is open for children from ages 0 - 18.

post_text:
March 14, 2020
After careful consideration and discussions, the Nettleton School District will cancel its classes next week, March 16-20, 2020. This decision was not made lightly, but the safety of our students and staff are the most important thing. All after-school activities and practices are suspended through at least March 22nd. All field trips are canceled indefinitely and all out of state school related travel is canceled indefinitely. Employees who work 235 days will report to work Monday and have a meeting at 8:15 in the HS library. Everyone should follow CDC and MS Department of Health guidelines to help minimize the spread of this pandemic. Thank you for your cooperation and patience as we deal with this issue.
Tim Dickerson
Superintendent
Nettleton School District
